data.title: MarkLines Automotive Industry Portal
data.text:
-The Company develops and manufactures systems and technologies to enable sustainable and connected mobility for people and goods. It provides brake systems, powertrain components and systems, chassis components and systems, safety systems, motion-control systems, display technologies, human-machine interfaces, interior sensing solutions, infotainment solutions, vehicle electronics and connectivity solutions, electric architecture solutions, tires, and technical elastomers.

-In the fiscal year ended December 31, 2023, sales to the automotive industry excluding the replacement business accounted for approximately 64% of the Company’s total sales.

-One aspect of the Company’s global strategy is to achieve increased balance of sales across all of its operating regions, thus allowing it to become less dependent on the European market. Specifically, the Company aims to generate more sales in emerging markets, particularly in Asia. This strategy can be seen in the trend of a steadily decreasing percentage of Company sales from Europe. The Company’s percentage of sales for Europe has decreased from 59.3% in the fiscal year ended December 31, 2011, to 48.5% in the fiscal year ended December 31, 2023.

-On January 1, 2022, the Company restructured its organization into four group sectors: Automotive, Tires, ContiTech and Contract Manufacturing. As of January 1, 2023, the Company’s Automotive group sector added a business area called Software and Central Technologies. On January 1, 2024, the Company dissolved the Smart Mobility business area within the Automotive group sector, reallocating its operations across other Automotive business areas. In addition, within the ContiTech group sector, the Advanced Dynamics Solutions, Conveying Solutions, Industrial Fluid Solutions, Mobile Fluid Systems, and Power Transmission Group business areas have been reorganized into three regional Industrial Solutions business areas and the Original Equipment Solutions business area as of January 1, 2024. Both the Tires and ContiTech are independent group sectors. Contract Manufacturing is both a group sector and business area, currently representing the contract manufacturing of products and systems by the Company for Vitesco Technologies. As of January 1, 2024, the Company’s organizational structure is divided into group sectors and business areas as follows:

-The Company completed the spin-off of Vitesco Technologies on September 15, 2021. Vitesco Technologies announced its successful market debut with the start of trading of its shares on the Frankfurt Stock Exchange. With the completion of the spin-off, Vitesco Technologies, the former Powertrain business area of the Company, has become independent.
